{{Infobox language |name=Shihhi Arabic |states=[[United Arab Emirates]], [[Oman]] |speakers=15,000 |date=2001-2003 |ref=<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/ssh|title=Arabic, Shihhi Spoken|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en}}</ref> |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Semitic languages|Semitic]] |fam3=[[Central Semitic languages|Central Semitic]] |fam4=[[Arabic languages|Arabic]] |fam5=[[Peninsular Arabic|Peninsular]] |iso3=ssh |glotto=shih1239 |glottorefname=Shihhi Arabic }}
'''Shihhi Arabic''' (also known as Shehhi, Shihu, Shihuh, or Al-Shihuh) is a [[Varieties of Arabic|variety]] of [[Arabic language|Arabic]] spoken in the [[Musandam Governorate]] of [[Oman]] and [[Ras al Khaimah]] emirate of [[UAE]].<ref>Raymond G. Gordon Jr., ed. 2005. ''Ethnologue: Languages of the World''. 15th edition. Dallas: Summer Institute of Linguistics.</ref>
